'''The Book of Cynog''' ({{lang-lat-med|Liber Knauc}}; {{lang-wlm|Llyfr Kynawc}}; {{lang-cy|Llyfr Cynog}}) was a text of [[medieval Wales|medieval]] [[Welsh law]].<ref>Wade-Evans, Arthur. ''Welsh Medieval Law'', [[s:Page:Welsh Medieval Law.djvu/445|p. 343]].</ref> It is quoted extensively by surviving sources but does not appear to have survived intact. However, the first 75 folios of Peniarth MS. 35 seem to be a medieval attempt to reconstruct the earlier book.<ref>Wiliam, Aled Rhys. "[http://welshjournals.llgc.org.uk/browse/viewobject/llgc-id:1288174/article/000037498 Restoration of the Book of Cynog]". ''National Library of Wales Journal'', Vol. 25, No. 3 (1988), p. 245{{ndash}}256. Accessed 27 Feb 2013.</ref>

