'''Fishpond Ltd.''' is a [[New Zealand]] [[e-commerce]] company based in [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]]. It was one of the first major companies to sell books over the [[Internet]] in New Zealand. Founded by Daniel Robertson in 2004, Fishpond.co.nz is a full-scale online bookstore. It also sells [[DVD]]s, music [[Compact Disc|CD]]s, games and gaming software as well as [[Toy]]s. In mid 2013, it had nearly 13 millions items in its catalogue, and made 20,000 sales per day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/business/8815405/Fishpond-baits-its-hook-with-more-picks|title=Fishpond baits its hook with more picks|first=Rob|last=Stock|date=23 June 2013|publisher=Fairfax New Zealand}}</ref>

Fishpond.com.au has established a separate website in [[Australia]].

==Locations==
The company is headquartered  in [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]] with staff located across Auckland, [[Christchurch]], Melbourne and Perth. It maintains software development centers in Auckland and Christchurch.

